                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/494: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-20T21:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1921—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. Received from President Zayas today incomplete and unsatiszfactory statement
                    of national finances. Have accumulated considerable data from other sources and
                    have secured services of an American expert accountant to analyze and complete
                    the statement. President Zayas is of the opinion that the necessity for a
                    foreign loan is not yet demonstrated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
